Latest News

  • Scottish Apprenticeship Week Mar 07, 2019

    Cabinet Secretary for Justice Mr Humza Yousaf MSP met with apprentices from the Scottish Courts and Tribunals Service (SCTS) today, as part of Skills Development Scotland Scottish Apprenticeship Week. Read more ...

  • Criminal Courts figures published Mar 07, 2019

    The third Scottish Courts and Tribunals Service statistical bulletin providing quarterly Official Statistics on criminal case activity in Scotland is published today. Read more ...

  • Dangerous dog fines dodgers feel the bite Feb 28, 2019

    Fines enforcement officers put the bite on fines dodgers who owed large sums of money for failing to keep their dangerous dogs under control, successfully recovering the unpaid monies. A new report released by SCTS today reveals that the fines collection rate remains consistently strong. Read more ...

All news...

Follow @SCTScourtstribs

Civil Online 


Civil Online is a secure online service that enables you to access information about your simple procedure case. Visit Civil Online.

Juror Information Film

SCTS has produced an information film which shows the different stages of the jury experience.  Watch the  juror information film

Reforming the Summary Criminal Court Process

A New Model for Summary Criminal Court Procedure published in February 2017. This paper proposes a new core model for summary court procedure which places digital technology and strong case management at the heart of the process.
Read the Evidence and Procedure Review

New Simple Procedure

Simple Procedure replaces the current small claims procedure and part of the summary cause procedure.  It is a court process designed to provide a speedy, inexpensive and informal way to resolve disputes where the monetary value does not exceed £5,000.
Read more on Simple Procedure
